President Donald Trump speaks about the coronavirus in the James Brady Press Briefing Room of the White House, Thursday, April 16, 2020, in Washington.
(Photo: Alex Brandon, AP)“A national shutdown is not a sustainable long-term solution,” Trump said Thursday at his daily White House news conference.
Testing WeaknessThe overarching weakness of Trump’s plan is that the U.S. still lacks sufficient testing capacity to know with much precision where the virus is spreading.
“It’s going to be very dependent on the governor,” Trump said.
“This is uncharted water,” he said at the White House news conference.